{
  "texts": [
    "Table 3 in Appendix lists the corresponding confusion matrix entries for the model predictions (first four rows) and values of the 18 evaluation metrics.",
    "The results indicate that all evaluation metrics rank naive random guess as the worst performing model.",
    "GBM is most frequently ranked as the best model, random forest is most frequently ranked as the second best.",
    "GLM is most frequently ranked as either third or fourth, and KNN is most frequently ranked as fifth but occasionally as third or fourth.",
    "LDA is ranked between third, fourth, and fifth or 1.5."
  ]
}